  "rationale": "<p>Choice C is correct. It is given that <span class=\"italic\">x</span> represents the number of stations that will be set up for Experiment A and that there will be 5 stations total, so it follows that 5 &ndash; <span class=\"italic\">x</span> is the number of stations that will be set up for Experiment B. It is also given that Experiment A requires 6 teaspoons of salt and that Experiment B requires 4 teaspoons of salt, so the total number of teaspoons of salt required is 6<span class=\"italic\">x</span> + 4(5 &ndash; <span class=\"italic\">x</span>), which simplifies to 2<span class=\"italic\">x</span> + 20.<p>Choices A, B, and D are incorrect and may be the result of not understanding the description of the context.</p></p>\n",
